Specifically, we have a chart label / data set JSON that is int he form.


```
  hpData: {
            day: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [60], labels: [60] },
            week: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [54], labels: [54] },
            month: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [57], labels: [57] },
            year: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [40], labels: [40] }
        }
```

We have an event handler that selects between the different time periods in the above object and displays them on a chart. The issue is that when the selection occurs between e.g. from month to week, the week `data` array gets stored in the month `data` array. And results in the following:


```
  hpData: {
            day: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [60], labels: [60] },
            week: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [54], labels: [54] },
            month: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [54], labels: [57] },
            year: { percentChange: &#39;&#39;, data: [40], labels: [40] }
        }
```

The month data array has been set to `data[54]` from `data[57]`. This occurs only when switching from month to another time interval. Our default state on first render is month.

