If you want the value in session to stay in sync with the database, you&#39;ll need to update both at the same time.

This would be done in your `pointshand.php` file where you handle the form submit and DB update. This is best done in a transaction to avoid race conditions on your data. For example

```php
$buycshamt = $_POST[&#39;buycshamt&#39;];
$sid = $_SESSION[&#39;userid&#39;];
$pdo-&gt;beginTransaction();
try {
    $stmt = $pdo-&gt;prepare(&#39;UPDATE users2 SET upoints = upoints + ? WHERE userid = ?&#39;);
    $stmt-&gt;bindParam(1, $buycshamt, PDO::PARAM_INT); // make sure it&#39;s handled as an int
    $stmt-&gt;bindParam(2, $sid);
    $stmt-&gt;execute();
    
    // fetch the updated value
    $stmt = $pdo-&gt;prepare(&#39;SELECT upoints FROM users2 WHERE userid = ?&#39;);
    $stmt-&gt;execute([$sid]);
    $_SESSION[&#39;upoints&#39;] = $stmt-&gt;fetchColumn(); // update the value in the session
    $pdo-&gt;commit();

    header(&#39;Location: index.php&#39;);
    exit();
} catch (PDOException $e) {
    $pdo-&gt;rollBack();
    throw $e;
}
```

